uk.ac.susx.mlcl.lib.collect
Class SparseDoubleVector

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.susx.mlcl.lib.collect.SparseVector
      uk.ac.susx.mlcl.lib.collect.SparseDoubleVector
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable
public final class SparseDoubleVector
extends SparseVector
implements Cloneable, Serializable

Store a sparse vector of double precision values as an ordered array non-zero indices and an ordered array of values. This is an ideal representation for performing fast dot product, or any other operation that ignores zero values, if the denisity is sufficiently low. Other operations can be slower than a full vector because indicies must be searched for.

Author:
Hamish Morgan <hamish.morgan@sussex.ac.uk>
